 [:p "The Company may additionally release personal, or other relevant information to third parties if it is required or compelled to do so to (a) satisfy any applicable law, regulation, legal process, or enforceable governmental request like a court order or order by a government; (b) enforce applicable Terms of Service, including investigation of potential violations thereof, such as preventing disruptive behavior; (c) detect, prevent or otherwise address fraud, security, or technical issues, such as scammers or hackers; or (d) protect against imminent harm to the rights, property, or safety of the Company, its users, or the public as required or permitted by law. Such as to investigate threats of violence or harm to our users, employees, or any other person."]
 [:p "Please note that we are a U.S. based company, and all of our data servers and all saved data are located in the United States. If you are a non-resident of the United States, please be aware that your personal data will be saved in these U.S. servers and will be subject to U.S. laws and jurisdiction. However, we are currently compliant with the EU General Data Protection Regulation, and at no time will your data will be protected under at least the minimum standards required under the General Data Protection Regulation and any other applicable U.S. Privacy Law."]
